{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YH1yoJQXbqXUcByBrwXA9e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→BUNS\n     2→ssekart\n     3→alled out into names.\n     4→The\n     5→favoured by\n     6→the julgalt.\n     7→ly named as you e right, esting n on\n     8→cover the bun\n     9→ver\n    10→Before raisins back\n    11→baking.\n    12→and leave into\n    13→the rising.\n    14→Preheat the oven to 225°C/435-VI0..\n    15→Brush the buns lightly\n    16→Bake until nicely\n    17→Bakc\n    18→golden.\n    19→or they will be the driest\n    20→The cooking time\n    21→The cod\n    22→shape you have made but should be 15 minutes.\n    23→Types of bun shapes, from\n    24→Lop\n    25→right: gullvagn. fuvagn, lessekarz tank\n    26→lilja. julgalt, and julkuse.\n    27→hila./\n    28→For image see page 279\n    29→FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\n    30→eden)\n    31→ing time: 2 hours\n    32→5)\n    33→utter\n    34→ablespoons)\n    35→1)\n    36→190\n    37→oz (to cup) segar\n    38→plan i tateleypo\n    39→extra for dusting\n    40→up rong wheat Bour, pl\n    41→135 g/415 oz (1 stick) butter, at room\n    42→Bes Wash (pages 73 4)\n    43→For the topping raisins, soaked in water pearl sugar, to taste\n    44→for at least an hour.\n    45→Add the saffron to the vodka and leave to infuse\n    46→Meanwhile, make the dough. Melt the butter in a pan age. Disson heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the salt, 1 tablespoon of the sugar and most of the four and work with the dough hook for 5-10 min-utes.\n    47→Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and\n    48→leave the dough to rise for 1 hour.\n    49→Stir the butter with the remaining sugar in a bowl until fuffy, then add the egg and the saffron and vodka infusion and stir. When the dough has finished rising, add the saffron and butter mix and the rest of the four while working the dough with the dough hook in the stand mixer.\n    50→Line 2 baking sheets with baking (parchment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute. Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron buns (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking cover with clean dish towels and leave to\n    51→rise for 30 minutes.\n    52→Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 220°C/425°F/Gas Mark 7. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle with raisins and/or pearl sugar. Bake for about to minutes, then leave to cool on wire racks.\n    53→For image see page 279\n    54→SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\n    55→/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\n    56→trutter med kesells / kurg (Sweden\n    57→Preparation and cooking rime 2 hour ising rime: r5s hour\n    58→Makes: 30 buns\n    59→100 g/3 oz (7 tablespoons) butter\n    60→500ml/17 fl oz (2 cups plus 2 tablespoons) milk\n    61→50g/2 oz fresh yeast (pages 58-61)\n    62→250 g/g oz. (1 cup) quark or cottage cheese\n    63→1 g/o.04 oz saffron (page 75)\n    64→150 g/5 oz (¼ cup) sugar\n    65→1 teaspoon salt\n    66→950g/2 lb 2 oz (7½ cups) strong wheat flour. plus extra for dusting\n    67→Egg Wash (pages 73-4)\n    68→To decorate\n    69→raisins, soaked in water and drained pearl sugar, to sprinkle\n    70→Melt the butter in a pan, then add the milk and heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the quark, saffron. sugar, salt and most of the flour and work the dough with the dough hook, starting at low speed. for 5-10 minutes. Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and leave to rise for 45 minutes.\n    71→Line several baking sheets with baking (parch-ment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute.\n    72→Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron bun (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking sheets, cover with clean dish towels and leave to rise for another 45 minutes.\n    73→Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 200°C/400°F/Gas Mark 6. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle on the raisins and pearl sugar to decorate.\n    74→Bake for about 1o minutes, or until golden. Leave to cool on wire racks.\n    75→For image see page 279\n    76→277 Recipes / Sweet pastries leavened with yeast"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78d44a45-0b0c-4a81-8a48-4c171bc96d81","uuid":"da88f62b-3dd0-470d-948c-d17fee769e66","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D).real.txt","content":"BUNS\nssekart\nalled out into names.\nThe\nfavoured by\nthe julgalt.\nly named as you e right, esting n on\ncover the bun\nver\nBefore raisins back\nbaking.\nand leave into\nthe rising.\nPreheat the oven to 225°C/435-VI0..\nBrush the buns lightly\nBake until nicely\nBakc\ngolden.\nor they will be the driest\nThe cooking time\nThe cod\nshape you have made but should be 15 minutes.\nTypes of bun shapes, from\nLop\nright: gullvagn. fuvagn, lessekarz tank\nlilja. julgalt, and julkuse.\nhila./\nFor image see page 279\nFRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\neden)\ning time: 2 hours\n5)\nutter\nablespoons)\n1)\n190\noz (to cup) segar\nplan i tateleypo\nextra for dusting\nup rong wheat Bour, pl\n135 g/415 oz (1 stick) butter, at room\nBes Wash (pages 73 4)\nFor the topping raisins, soaked in water pearl sugar, to taste\nfor at least an hour.\nAdd the saffron to the vodka and leave to infuse\nMeanwhile, make the dough. Melt the butter in a pan age. Disson heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the salt, 1 tablespoon of the sugar and most of the four and work with the dough hook for 5-10 min-utes.\nCover the bowl with a clean dish towel and\nleave the dough to rise for 1 hour.\nStir the butter with the remaining sugar in a bowl until fuffy, then add the egg and the saffron and vodka infusion and stir. When the dough has finished rising, add the saffron and butter mix and the rest of the four while working the dough with the dough hook in the stand mixer.\nLine 2 baking sheets with baking (parchment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute. Divide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron buns (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking cover with clean dish towels and leave to\nrise for 30 minutes.\nMeanwhile, preheat the oven to 220°C/425°F/Gas Mark 7. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle with raisins and/or pearl sugar. Bake for about to minutes, then leave to cool on wire racks.\nFor image see page 279\nSAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\n/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\ntrutter med kesells / kurg (Sweden\nPreparation and cooking rime 2 hour ising rime: r5s hour\nMakes: 30 buns\n100 g/3 oz (7 tablespoons) butter\n500ml/17 fl oz (2 cups plus 2 tablespoons) milk\n50g/2 oz fresh yeast (pages 58-61)\n250 g/g oz. (1 cup) quark or cottage cheese\n1 g/o.04 oz saffron (page 75)\n150 g/5 oz (¼ cup) sugar\n1 teaspoon salt\n950g/2 lb 2 oz (7½ cups) strong wheat flour. plus extra for dusting\nEgg Wash (pages 73-4)\nTo decorate\nraisins, soaked in water and drained pearl sugar, to sprinkle\nMelt the butter in a pan, then add the milk and heat to body temperature (37°C/98.6°F). Dissolve the yeast in the milk and butter mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer. Add the quark, saffron. sugar, salt and most of the flour and work the dough with the dough hook, starting at low speed. for 5-10 minutes. Cover the bowl with a clean dish towel and leave to rise for 45 minutes.\nLine several baking sheets with baking (parch-ment) paper. Tip the dough out onto a lightly floured work counter and knead it for a minute.\nDivide the dough into 30 equal pieces and shape them into your choice of saffron bun (see illustrations opposite). Put the buns on the prepared baking sheets, cover with clean dish towels and leave to rise for another 45 minutes.\nMeanwhile, preheat the oven to 200°C/400°F/Gas Mark 6. Brush the buns with the egg wash and sprinkle on the raisins and pearl sugar to decorate.\nBake for about 1o minutes, or until golden. Leave to cool on wire racks.\nFor image see page 279\n277 Recipes / Sweet pastries leavened with yeast","numLines":76,"startLine":1,"totalLines":76}}}
